    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-07T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-07T07:00:00-05:00" n="787"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d787">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.1115/2191: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-07T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 7, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received November 7—11:05
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. Line damaged and unable as yet to telephone Department’s 33 and 34 to
                        Vigo.<note n="83" xml:id="d787fn83">Neither printed.</note> Stewart brought
                    following message from Graves: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Just received word from Auditor General at Coruna that Celaya<note
                                n="84" xml:id="d787fn84">See telegram of October 17, 1 p.m., from
                                the Consul General at Lisbon, <ref target="#pg_739">p.
                                739</ref>.</note> will be tried by court martial at Lugo Wednesday,
                            November 11. Understand either death sentence or life imprisonment will
                            be requested. Am planning to be present at court martial.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Department’s 33 and 34 delivered personally to Stewart.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
